<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>Shell by Example</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="site.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="index">
        <h2>Shell by Example</h2>

        <p class="intro">
            <em>Shell by Example</em> is a hands-on introduction to shell scripting
            using annotated example programs. Check out the first example or browse
            the full list below.
        </p>

        <p class="intro">
            Examples marked with <span class="label label-posix">POSIX</span> work
            in any POSIX-compliant shell (sh, dash, bash, zsh, etc.).
            Examples marked with <span class="label label-bash">Bash</span> require
            Bash-specific features.
        </p>

        <ul>
            {{range .}}
            <li>
                <a href="{{.ID}}.html">{{.Name}}</a>
                {{if .IsBash}}<span class="label label-bash">Bash</span>{{else}}<span class="label label-posix">POSIX</span>{{end}}
            </li>
            {{end}}
        </ul>

        <p class="footer">
            by <a href="https://josediazgonzalez.com">Jose Diaz-Gonzalez</a>
            | inspired by <a href="https://gobyexample.com">Go by Example</a>
            | <a href="https://github.com/josegonzalez/shellbyexample.com">source</a>
        </p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
